1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:03,545
I am Uhtred, son of Uhtred.

2
00:00:04,296 --> 00:00:05,589
My lifelong ambition

3
00:00:05,672 --> 00:00:10,511
to take back my birthright to Bebbanburg
has ended in failure.

4
00:00:10,594 --> 00:00:11,762
Beoccal.

5
00:00:11,845 --> 00:00:15,974
He is with God now. He is at peace.

6
00:00:16,058 --> 00:00:20,395
While I struggle fo come to terms
with this devastating loss,

7
00:00:20,479 --> 00:00:24,358
Haesten has revealed
the true cause of Ragnar's death.

8
00:00:26,276 --> 00:00:29,363
Let me live and I'll tell you
who gave the command.

9
00:00:29,446 --> 00:00:31,365
- Speak.
- Cnut.

10
00:00:32,991 --> 00:00:36,745
But Brida knows nothing
of Cnuts treachery...

11
00:00:36,828 --> 00:00:39,915
and prepares fo ride info battle with him.

12
00:00:39,998 --> 00:00:44,169
When the kings are dead,
we will sit together on Alfred's throne.

13
00:00:44,253 --> 00:00:50,384
Aethelred, blinded by lust and power,
has foolishly invaded Daneland.

14
00:00:51,260 --> 00:00:54,805
Cnut did not sail to Irland.
Haesten gave me false information.

15
00:00:54,888 --> 00:00:58,308
- You must tell Aethelred the truth!
- If I tell him the truth, he will kill me.

16
00:00:58,850 --> 00:01:01,353
I will do all I can to soften the blow.

17
00:01:01,436 --> 00:01:06,149
Aethelhelm's influence on Edward
has caused conflict in Winchester.

18
00:01:06,233 --> 00:01:07,776
These are my people.

19
00:01:07,859 --> 00:01:12,322
I will not send them to be slaughtered
while Cnut sets the terms of the battle!

20
00:01:13,407 --> 00:01:16,618
You will take a message to the Welsh King.

21
00:01:16,702 --> 00:01:20,706
Aethelflaed is expecting an army.
We must deliver one.

22
00:01:21,915 --> 00:01:27,087
I have taken Cnut's sons as my prisoners
and brought them to Aethelflaed...

23
00:01:27,170 --> 00:01:30,716
fo be used as bait in the battle
I know is fo come.

24
00:01:33,010 --> 00:01:34,761
Destiny is all!

25
00:02:13,342 --> 00:02:15,427
The monastery is two miles south.

26
00:02:16,011 --> 00:02:17,721
I am not looking for the monastery.

27
00:02:18,639 --> 00:02:21,516
- Saxons are not welcome here, Father.
- I know.

28
00:02:21,600 --> 00:02:23,769
But I've urgent business with King Hywel.

29
00:02:25,103 --> 00:02:28,357
- Are you Saxon?
- Well, I was born a Briton.

30
00:02:28,440 --> 00:02:30,275
You will only find trouble here, Brother.

31
00:02:30,359 --> 00:02:33,654
You will find more than trouble
if you do not let me pass.

32
00:02:47,876 --> 00:02:51,129
Oh, Lord,
grant us the knowledge of your power

33
00:02:51,213 --> 00:02:55,217
when it comes to pass that a man and wife
may bring a child into this world.

34
00:02:55,300 --> 00:02:59,680
They clothe him. They cherish him,
but God alone may know his fate.

35
00:02:59,763 --> 00:03:01,181
These children were in darkness.

36
00:03:01,264 --> 00:03:03,517
Now they are saved.

37
00:03:04,142 --> 00:03:06,269
Bring them the light of your love,
Lord God...

38
00:03:06,895 --> 00:03:09,147
and let them walk as children of light.

39
00:03:09,648 --> 00:03:11,650
Where are they? Why is she not ready?

40
00:03:13,694 --> 00:03:15,278
They mourn the dead.

41
00:03:15,362 --> 00:03:19,533
Than he who considers
before his soul's departure

42
00:03:19,616 --> 00:03:21,993
how worthy he may be deemed
after his death...

43
00:03:22,077 --> 00:03:23,662
There is no time for this.

44
00:03:25,539 --> 00:03:27,916
They are children, Uhtred.

45
00:03:28,291 --> 00:03:31,002
Sons of Mercia's most revered men.

46
00:03:32,462 --> 00:03:34,965
When did children become the cost of war?

47
00:03:38,844 --> 00:03:40,595
You did all that you could.

48
00:03:42,180 --> 00:03:43,265
Now, come.

49
00:03:44,516 --> 00:03:47,728
- They took their heads.
- All of them.

50
00:03:54,901 --> 00:03:58,071
We must move off before the Danes
know that you are here.

51
00:03:58,155 --> 00:04:00,031
Not until they have been blessed!

52
00:04:00,115 --> 00:04:03,660
- Aethelflaed, please...
- Not until they have been blessed!

53
00:04:03,744 --> 00:04:06,955
Danes! The Danes are here, Lord!

54
00:04:08,248 --> 00:04:11,042
- They're heading towards the gates!
- How many?

55
00:04:11,126 --> 00:04:12,169
Too many, Lord!

56
00:04:12,252 --> 00:04:13,295
Stay back, Aethelflaed.

57
00:04:13,378 --> 00:04:17,007
Seeing you will inflame them.
Go! Upstairs now!

58
00:04:17,090 --> 00:04:19,885
- They got past the entrance!
- Go. We will hold them off.

59
00:04:36,860 --> 00:04:41,114
Give me the Lady
and you will not be slaughtered!

60
00:04:41,823 --> 00:04:43,325
Do not even consider it!

61
00:04:43,408 --> 00:04:47,204
- I will not have men murdered in my place!
- I will not see you taken!

62
00:04:47,287 --> 00:04:51,917
You have the word of Cnut!
He only wants Alfred's daughter!

63
00:04:54,252 --> 00:04:56,254
- Is there another way out?
- No!

64
00:04:57,005 --> 00:04:59,466
- Can we get to the roof?
- We would only get trapped.

65
00:04:59,549 --> 00:05:02,552
- Let me bargain.
- Lady, you are the bargain.

66
00:05:02,636 --> 00:05:05,931
We cannot just let death
come to us. I will not just wait for it.

67
00:05:06,014 --> 00:05:09,309
What are we doing, Lord?
The door will not hold!

68
00:05:09,392 --> 00:05:11,436
- Bring me Cnut's sons.
- Sihtric!

69
00:05:11,520 --> 00:05:13,814
Uhtred, you cannot.
There will be another way.

70
00:05:13,897 --> 00:05:15,899
You must trust me and you must swear

71
00:05:15,982 --> 00:05:18,902
- to me you will stay here. Swear to me!
- Do not do this...

72
00:05:22,030 --> 00:05:23,949
Where is she?

73
00:05:28,161 --> 00:05:29,788
Kill them all!

74
00:05:30,205 --> 00:05:31,790
Enough!

75
00:05:35,836 --> 00:05:37,170
Come and face me.

76
00:05:42,843 --> 00:05:44,427
I have Cnut's sons.

77
00:05:47,389 --> 00:05:48,515
You are lying.

78
00:05:57,399 --> 00:05:59,985
Leave this place
or I will cut their throats!

79
00:06:00,652 --> 00:06:01,987
Take a son of Cnut...

80
00:06:02,696 --> 00:06:04,948
every Dane in this land
will see it avenged!

81
00:06:05,031 --> 00:06:07,075
Yes, and every Dane
will come for you, too.

82
00:06:07,158 --> 00:06:09,035
The blood of his child
will be on your hands.

83
00:06:09,119 --> 00:06:11,037
Do not play games.

84
00:06:11,121 --> 00:06:15,000
Send them down now...
or all the men here will be killed.

85
00:06:15,083 --> 00:06:17,419
Leave this place
or I will cut off their heads!

86
00:06:17,502 --> 00:06:20,130
You harm them and every Saxon here dies!

87
00:06:21,673 --> 00:06:23,049
No!

88
00:06:24,217 --> 00:06:27,178
No!

89
00:06:35,020 --> 00:06:37,689
No!

90
00:06:41,735 --> 00:06:43,236
No!

91
00:06:43,320 --> 00:06:44,571
Leave!

92
00:06:45,697 --> 00:06:47,532
Or I will kill the other one also!

93
00:06:49,075 --> 00:06:50,160
Go!

94
00:06:50,911 --> 00:06:52,996
- Now...
- Go!

95
00:07:02,589 --> 00:07:03,673
No!

96
00:07:04,215 --> 00:07:07,218
Stay down. Look! Your brother's alive.

97
00:07:55,517 --> 00:07:58,895
Cnut will hunt us
as soon as he gets word I killed his boy.

98
00:07:59,604 --> 00:08:03,191
- Surely we just show that they are alive?
- Danes do not work like that.

99
00:08:03,817 --> 00:08:05,235
We're now headed for battle.

100
00:08:05,318 --> 00:08:06,361
What about the boys?

101
00:08:06,444 --> 00:08:08,947
Cut them free and let them run.
They've served their purpose.

102
00:08:09,030 --> 00:08:11,282
And was the purpose
to enrage a Danish army?

103
00:08:11,366 --> 00:08:14,703
It bought us time
and allowed us to escape with our lives.

104
00:08:14,786 --> 00:08:17,080
Fate wants to drag us
to fight for the Saxons.

105
00:08:17,163 --> 00:08:20,375
Yes. It was definitely fate
that dragged us into all of this.

106
00:08:20,458 --> 00:08:22,168
Uhtred had nothing to do with it.

107
00:08:22,252 --> 00:08:25,171
I do not seek battles.
Battles just seem to seek me.

108
00:08:26,631 --> 00:08:29,134
But you are right,
I have unleashed a storm.

109
00:08:29,217 --> 00:08:32,429
Cnut will find us. This is now our fight.

110
00:08:32,512 --> 00:08:36,349
It was our fight from the moment
you took those boys from Haesten, Lord.

111
00:08:41,146 --> 00:08:43,565
The men would be forgiven
for abandoning me.

112
00:08:44,107 --> 00:08:47,360
They like an adventure
and they're loyal to a good leader.

113
00:08:48,278 --> 00:08:49,320
As are you.

114
00:08:58,538 --> 00:09:00,790
Which is the fastest road to Tettenhall?

115
00:09:17,390 --> 00:09:20,060
Do not fear the beast. He's been fed.

116
00:09:21,311 --> 00:09:24,064
- Does he like strangers?
- Only when cooked.

117
00:09:28,443 --> 00:09:32,197
You are from the boy king in Wessex?
Why do you come crawling before us?

118
00:09:32,947 --> 00:09:35,033
Wessex would like to strike a bargain.

119
00:09:35,116 --> 00:09:37,619
I do not make treaties with Saxons.

120
00:09:37,702 --> 00:09:39,954
Nevertheless, we have an offer.

121
00:09:41,039 --> 00:09:44,834
There is concern in Wessex about Cnut
and his incursion into Mercia.

122
00:09:44,918 --> 00:09:49,214
Alfred's actions have bitten Edward
on the arse. So?

123
00:09:49,297 --> 00:09:52,133
Cnut's army is slaughtering
all in their path.

124
00:09:53,009 --> 00:09:57,806
You are not friends to us, Father Pyrlig.
Why should any of this concern me?

125
00:09:58,389 --> 00:10:01,226
Because it brings a dangerous heathen
to your border.

126
00:10:01,309 --> 00:10:04,604
And yet, our borders are strong...

127
00:10:04,687 --> 00:10:07,690
because we've been repelling Saxons
for years.

128
00:10:09,859 --> 00:10:13,029
As you know, Alfred wanted
all the Christian kingdoms to unite.

129
00:10:13,530 --> 00:10:17,200
Yes, under his banner,
so we could all bow to him.

130
00:10:17,283 --> 00:10:19,953
He wanted to conquer, not unite the faith.

131
00:10:20,036 --> 00:10:22,413
Nevertheless that faith
is now under threat.

132
00:10:23,414 --> 00:10:25,625
We follow the same one God
and share a common enemy.

133
00:10:25,708 --> 00:10:29,087
You know that, Lord King.
And you know to repel Cnut now

134
00:10:29,170 --> 00:10:33,299
will save you bloodshed later, so,
it is a bargain that works for both of us.

135
00:10:40,014 --> 00:10:41,683
What are Edward's plans?

136
00:10:43,268 --> 00:10:45,311
Mercians are gathering at Tettenhall.

137
00:10:46,104 --> 00:10:49,315
There are... plans
for Wessex to join them.

138
00:10:50,483 --> 00:10:55,238
And what would I get in return,
in this holy war against the pagans?

139
00:10:55,321 --> 00:10:57,949
And do not tell me recompense in heaven.

140
00:10:58,533 --> 00:11:01,411
Celestial rewards do not build fortresses.

141
00:11:03,830 --> 00:11:05,165
What is it you want?

142
00:11:05,248 --> 00:11:11,504
The spoils of battle, all of them,
every last piece of Danish silver.

143
00:11:12,338 --> 00:11:14,924
That is not a promise
I have the authority to make.

144
00:11:15,925 --> 00:11:19,512
You are here on Edward's orders,
you must have his authority.

145
00:11:21,598 --> 00:11:23,600
Do I have your promise, Father Pyrlig?

146
00:11:27,187 --> 00:11:28,688
Let him swear upon the book.

147
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:55,089
Eardwulf!

148
00:11:57,133 --> 00:11:59,260
What news of our troops in Lindcylne?

149
00:11:59,344 --> 00:12:03,223
The settlements that surround it
are resisting, Lord, but we will prevail.

150
00:12:03,306 --> 00:12:04,766
I should hope so.

151
00:12:06,184 --> 00:12:10,605
I want all of East Anglia
or our bargain does not hold.

152
00:12:11,314 --> 00:12:13,816
It would be a shame for your family
to go unrewarded.

153
00:12:17,445 --> 00:12:18,780
After so much effort!

154
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:32,627
He's like a pig rolling in shit.

155
00:12:33,670 --> 00:12:37,423
Ask me nothing of the detail.
It was a favor to you, not to him.

156
00:12:38,633 --> 00:12:41,719
It is enough that humping me
has lifted his spirits.

157
00:12:42,387 --> 00:12:44,264
So, you must tell him
the news from Mercia.

158
00:12:47,642 --> 00:12:49,727
- Perhaps I should delay...
- You cannot put it off.

159
00:12:51,354 --> 00:12:55,233
I know you are afraid,
but I have bought us some goodwill.

160
00:12:55,316 --> 00:12:58,069
- I'm not afraid. I'm just...
- You are afraid and so am I.

161
00:12:59,237 --> 00:13:02,865
But I have done my part, brother.
Now you do yours.

162
00:13:38,276 --> 00:13:41,571
- Do not let me win, Steapa.
- Lord, I am not.

163
00:13:45,283 --> 00:13:46,534
What has happened?

164
00:13:53,958 --> 00:13:56,586
The settlements around Lindcylne
have capitulated.

165
00:13:57,337 --> 00:13:59,297
If you want to see some hands,
it can be arranged.

166
00:14:03,593 --> 00:14:05,511
And what's the bad news?

167
00:14:07,096 --> 00:14:09,349
You are clearly waiting
to deliver bad news.

168
00:14:13,061 --> 00:14:14,854
News has come from Edward, Lord King.

169
00:14:16,230 --> 00:14:19,317
I regret to tell you that Cnut's armies
have raided Mercia

170
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:21,152
and taken your palace at Aegelesburg.

171
00:14:25,531 --> 00:14:28,493
Is this the same Cnut
that you told me was heading to Irland...

172
00:14:29,619 --> 00:14:31,454
to help some feral cousin?

173
00:14:32,747 --> 00:14:33,831
Yes, Lord.

174
00:14:33,915 --> 00:14:36,459
Because of whom
I left my kingdom undefended?

175
00:14:38,586 --> 00:14:39,921
And now it is in ruins?

176
00:14:40,004 --> 00:14:42,006
There was no reason
to mistrust the information.

177
00:14:42,090 --> 00:14:45,551
My spy in the Danish camp was certain.
He swore it was true.

178
00:14:46,469 --> 00:14:49,305
- Haesten is a close ally of...
- Did you say Haesten?

179
00:14:51,808 --> 00:14:53,688
- Yes, Lord. He's a close...
- I know who he is!

180
00:14:55,103 --> 00:14:56,854
He is well known to be a liar!

181
00:14:58,356 --> 00:15:02,068
You are nothing but a rat's turd,
who should never have been trusted

182
00:15:02,151 --> 00:15:03,778
with anything more than an ax!

183
00:15:05,905 --> 00:15:06,989
I pitied you...

184
00:15:09,033 --> 00:15:12,954
gave your whore of a sister the chance
to restore your family and this...

185
00:15:13,746 --> 00:15:15,164
is how you repay me.

186
00:15:17,667 --> 00:15:19,544
Only a fool would have trusted Haesten.

187
00:15:20,628 --> 00:15:25,383
- I know, but I've made a plan to retake...
- My reputation will be ripped to shreds!

188
00:15:25,466 --> 00:15:28,052
We've had word from Lady Aethelflaed.

189
00:15:28,136 --> 00:15:30,721
She will be at Tettenhall,
where she plans to lure Cnut.

190
00:15:30,805 --> 00:15:33,850
So now my wife is heading to battle
before me...

191
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:38,062
so that she can be revered
as the savior of my kingdom?

192
00:15:38,771 --> 00:15:41,482
How in the name of God
is that supposed to cheer me?

193
00:15:41,566 --> 00:15:43,109
I'm just saying that there is a plan.

194
00:15:44,068 --> 00:15:47,905
Lord, there is advantage in this,
if you play it right,

195
00:15:47,989 --> 00:15:50,992
a chance to return to Mercia
as the avenging hero.

196
00:15:53,661 --> 00:15:57,665
Can the men get here by morning?

197
00:16:01,169 --> 00:16:06,299
Uh, yes, Lord. I can send orders
for them to return immediately.

198
00:16:07,967 --> 00:16:11,512
- This could be your greatest triumph...
- You are finished, Eardwulf!

199
00:16:13,514 --> 00:16:14,765
Please do not execute me.

200
00:16:14,849 --> 00:16:17,059
You will pray for execution.

201
00:16:18,644 --> 00:16:22,023
When we return to Aegelesburg,
I will publicly castrate you.

202
00:16:23,357 --> 00:16:27,987
And your family will never prosper
and your sister will never leave my bed.

203
00:16:50,968 --> 00:16:53,429
Why have you sent Father Pyrlig to Wealas?

204
00:16:54,889 --> 00:16:58,434
Do not lie to me, Mother. We have spies
in every court from here to Rome!

205
00:17:02,021 --> 00:17:06,442
Hywel has Danes,
rampaging near his borders.

206
00:17:06,526 --> 00:17:09,153
It is only right for Pyrlig
to alert him to it.

207
00:17:09,237 --> 00:17:12,031
Have you asked Hywel for help?

208
00:17:14,325 --> 00:17:16,452
That is unforgivable.

209
00:17:16,536 --> 00:17:18,037
I had to do something!

210
00:17:18,788 --> 00:17:22,291
Your sister has thrown herself
into the lion's mouth.

211
00:17:22,375 --> 00:17:24,085
I challenge any mother to act differently.

212
00:17:24,168 --> 00:17:27,588
You are not just any mother.
You are the mother of a king.

213
00:17:28,881 --> 00:17:33,094
Cnut wants us to march on his terms.
It is a trap you have walked into.

214
00:17:33,177 --> 00:17:37,807
But Hywel is a Christian,
and God wants us to be united.

215
00:17:37,890 --> 00:17:40,601
Hywel serves no one but his own people.

216
00:17:40,685 --> 00:17:43,896
In going to him,
you have made Wessex look divided.

217
00:17:43,980 --> 00:17:46,691
Cnut will hear of it
and think we are weak!

218
00:17:49,652 --> 00:17:53,990
Yes, but I want my daughter safe.

219
00:17:55,324 --> 00:17:58,202
Then you should have persuaded her
to stay in Wessex.

220
00:17:59,787 --> 00:18:03,833
My men would not forgive me for
chasing my sister into a hopeless battle.

221
00:18:04,667 --> 00:18:08,879
And yet you know they will also revile you
for letting her die.

222
00:18:09,463 --> 00:18:12,425
Like it or not,
Aethelflaed has forced your hand.

223
00:18:12,508 --> 00:18:16,012
So I trade the life of Wessex soldiers
for my own honor?

224
00:18:16,095 --> 00:18:19,765
That is what the soldiers are there for,
to do the King's bidding...

225
00:18:19,849 --> 00:18:22,226
Yes, but not the bidding
of the King's mother.

226
00:18:25,980 --> 00:18:29,859
Besides, it is too late.
Aethelflaed's fyrds are marching.

227
00:18:32,403 --> 00:18:35,615
You had word of that and did not tell me?

228
00:18:35,698 --> 00:18:38,576
You were elsewhere, making other plans.

229
00:18:41,245 --> 00:18:46,709
If you wanted
men to speak your name in awe,

230
00:18:46,792 --> 00:18:50,588
believe me, this was not the way.

231
00:19:18,699 --> 00:19:19,950
Lord.

232
00:19:20,034 --> 00:19:22,161
I want all of these defenses
finished by sunset.

233
00:19:22,244 --> 00:19:23,871
- Yes, My Lord.
- Good.

234
00:19:27,458 --> 00:19:28,668
We are so close, Brida...

235
00:19:30,044 --> 00:19:31,671
to everything we ever wanted.

236
00:19:34,006 --> 00:19:38,386
Lands for our people to settle in
for generations.

237
00:19:42,056 --> 00:19:43,140
Cnut?

238
00:19:44,850 --> 00:19:45,893
Yes.

239
00:19:51,190 --> 00:19:54,026
- There's something...
- Ah. It's Bjorgulf,

240
00:19:54,110 --> 00:19:56,362
returning with Alfred's little bitch.

241
00:20:04,912 --> 00:20:06,122
Where is Aethelflaed?

242
00:20:08,332 --> 00:20:09,458
She escaped.

243
00:20:11,085 --> 00:20:12,211
How did this happen?

244
00:20:16,257 --> 00:20:17,383
Tell us.

245
00:20:19,844 --> 00:20:21,887
Uhtred Ragnarson is in Aegelesburg.

246
00:20:23,639 --> 00:20:25,182
He had your sons with him.

247
00:20:25,266 --> 00:20:27,852
Haesten appears to have traded them
for his life.

248
00:20:29,061 --> 00:20:31,272
Tell me that my sons live.

249
00:20:34,024 --> 00:20:36,527
I will not harm you.
Just tell me the news.

250
00:20:55,546 --> 00:20:57,381
Uhtred beheaded your eldest son.

251
00:21:00,676 --> 00:21:04,513
He would have killed Esgar
had we not left.

252
00:21:10,436 --> 00:21:13,439
No! Why? Why?

253
00:21:16,901 --> 00:21:18,986
I want Uhtred Ragnarson taken immediately!

254
00:21:19,069 --> 00:21:21,489
- No.
- No one sleeps until he is found!

255
00:21:21,572 --> 00:21:24,825
No! This will be paid for in blood,
but we cannot let it distract us.

256
00:21:24,909 --> 00:21:27,244
Avenging my child is not a distraction!

257
00:21:27,328 --> 00:21:28,454
Jackdaw!

258
00:21:29,455 --> 00:21:34,502
Cnut, I share your grief and your anger.
The gods know I do.

259
00:21:34,585 --> 00:21:38,380
Please... do not let Uhtred lure you
into a fight. He's not the priority.

260
00:21:38,464 --> 00:21:39,673
He killed my firstborn

261
00:21:39,757 --> 00:21:41,425
and Esgar is still with him!

262
00:21:42,510 --> 00:21:45,137
- If I have no heir, all of this...
- Cnut.

263
00:21:45,221 --> 00:21:46,764
- All of this is for nothing!
- Cnut.

264
00:21:46,847 --> 00:21:48,641
Do not give up our battle position!

265
00:21:48,724 --> 00:21:53,270
It does not matter where we fight!
We have a thousand warriors!

266
00:21:53,354 --> 00:21:56,273
- Jackdaw! Prepare the men to march!
- I will.

267
00:21:56,357 --> 00:21:59,735
And send men ahead to find them!
We will follow... now!

268
00:22:00,444 --> 00:22:01,487
- Cnut...
- Leave me!

269
00:22:01,570 --> 00:22:03,405
This way is foolishness, Cnut!

270
00:22:03,489 --> 00:22:05,115
You find him, Jackdaw!

271
00:22:21,090 --> 00:22:22,174
You got a numb arse there?

272
00:22:28,013 --> 00:22:30,891
You get used to a numb arse
kneeling through church all day.

273
00:22:30,975 --> 00:22:32,685
It's a damp arse that kills you.

274
00:22:38,774 --> 00:22:40,943
What do you think will happen
when we face the Danes?

275
00:22:41,026 --> 00:22:44,154
A numb arse
will be the least of our problems.

276
00:22:45,197 --> 00:22:48,117
- We're good fighters.
- When we are all fit to fight.

277
00:22:49,118 --> 00:22:52,037
I have fought alongside your father
for a while now.

278
00:22:52,705 --> 00:22:56,792
And he tends to come up with something...
at the last minute.

279
00:22:57,376 --> 00:23:00,671
And many men are loyal to Aethelflaed,
even at their own cost.

280
00:23:00,754 --> 00:23:03,966
And no doubt the pair of them
are devising a battle plan to save us all.

281
00:23:25,029 --> 00:23:28,574
Not here. Not with them so close.

282
00:23:29,658 --> 00:23:32,828
You would deny yourself
the day before a fight?

283
00:23:32,912 --> 00:23:34,371
It gives me strength.

284
00:23:35,831 --> 00:23:37,374
What if you die on the battlefield?

285
00:23:40,210 --> 00:23:45,049
I will not die, because God favors those
with goodness in their hearts.

286
00:23:48,260 --> 00:23:49,553
Maybe.

287
00:23:49,637 --> 00:23:52,139
I believe the gods play with us.

288
00:23:53,599 --> 00:23:57,311
And we do not know their reasons
or what is destined for us.

289
00:23:59,980 --> 00:24:02,608
But tonight,
I will believe what you believe.

290
00:24:05,069 --> 00:24:07,363
I thought your destiny was Bebbanburg.

291
00:24:12,534 --> 00:24:13,911
I thought that.

292
00:24:16,664 --> 00:24:18,082
For so long.

293
00:24:23,337 --> 00:24:26,840
But now I ask myself why I failed there.

294
00:24:30,552 --> 00:24:34,056
I know there is a plan for me,
yet I do not know what it is.

295
00:24:37,935 --> 00:24:39,812
Only that it leads me to you.

296
00:24:41,355 --> 00:24:47,027
And Finan is right. I chose to be here,
so, that must mean something.

297
00:24:48,570 --> 00:24:52,408
It means that you care for the fate
of Mercia and the Saxons.

298
00:24:53,283 --> 00:24:54,785
Now you sound like your father.

299
00:24:56,829 --> 00:24:59,206
He only used me for his own wishes.

300
00:24:59,289 --> 00:25:02,710
Yes, he was a wise man,
and I tried to follow in his path.

301
00:25:02,793 --> 00:25:07,381
So, perhaps then, I, too,
should only use you for my wishes.

302
00:25:07,405 --> 00:25:15,405
http://hiqve.com/

303
00:25:45,794 --> 00:25:46,837
Edward...

304
00:25:47,588 --> 00:25:48,714
come and rest.

305
00:25:49,715 --> 00:25:51,633
God is guiding you. I know it.

306
00:25:55,971 --> 00:25:58,182
Do not turn away from all of your family.

307
00:25:59,433 --> 00:26:01,226
I know your son would like to see you.

308
00:26:01,977 --> 00:26:04,229
He often speaks fondly of you.

309
00:26:08,609 --> 00:26:11,153
A child without its father's guidance
will grow weak.

310
00:26:11,236 --> 00:26:13,906
Which is why
I endeavor to seek the Lord's help.

311
00:26:16,075 --> 00:26:17,868
So if you would leave me in peace.

312
00:26:37,137 --> 00:26:40,808
There's no point disturbing him.
He is still deep in prayer.

313
00:26:41,475 --> 00:26:43,769
He does not need divine guidance.

314
00:26:43,852 --> 00:26:46,814
He just needs to listen to those of us
that know the cost of battle.

315
00:26:46,897 --> 00:26:48,232
His mother's been advising him.

316
00:26:48,315 --> 00:26:51,902
Yes. I'm afraid
that's not all she's been doing.

317
00:26:53,487 --> 00:26:57,199
Lady Aelswith was seen visiting
Edward's bastard at the monastery.

318
00:26:57,282 --> 00:27:02,621
I am told she arranged a reunion
between the boy and his mother.

319
00:27:02,704 --> 00:27:08,043
Why? What business has she showing
kindness to a whore and her offspring?

320
00:27:08,127 --> 00:27:09,503
I do not know.

321
00:27:10,587 --> 00:27:14,633
But a rumor persists
that their marriage was legitimate.

322
00:27:15,592 --> 00:27:17,219
A false rumor.

323
00:27:17,302 --> 00:27:20,055
But still one that could endanger my son,
when the time comes.

324
00:27:23,809 --> 00:27:27,938
I trust
you are keeping your husband satisfied.

325
00:27:28,939 --> 00:27:31,358
Another son would strengthen our position.

326
00:27:32,151 --> 00:27:36,238
I try to, Father,
but he is not as attentive as he once was.

327
00:27:36,321 --> 00:27:39,032
The matters of Kingship
weigh heavy on him.

328
00:27:39,116 --> 00:27:41,994
Then you must try harder...

329
00:27:42,077 --> 00:27:47,875
because it is clear that Lady Aelswith
is following a plan of her own.

330
00:27:47,958 --> 00:27:49,668
Then you must do something to stop her,

331
00:27:49,751 --> 00:27:52,379
before she turns the King
from me and my son!

332
00:27:52,462 --> 00:27:55,757
I will do what I must. Trust me.

333
00:27:56,383 --> 00:28:01,388
I have not come this far
to be thwarted by a bitter widow.

334
00:28:37,591 --> 00:28:38,926
Is this the place?

335
00:28:39,551 --> 00:28:40,594
Yes.

336
00:28:41,136 --> 00:28:43,180
I'm not sure I can see Edward's camp.

337
00:28:44,264 --> 00:28:46,350
I'm not sure I can see anyone.

338
00:28:46,433 --> 00:28:47,976
He will be here.

339
00:29:12,626 --> 00:29:15,587
I sent word that the fyrds
should gather in the woods.

340
00:29:15,671 --> 00:29:18,465
I will ready them for battle
before my brother arrives.

341
00:29:20,759 --> 00:29:21,802
Lord.

342
00:29:22,719 --> 00:29:23,762
Men!

343
00:29:27,266 --> 00:29:30,269
- That is not a fyrd.
- And they are not Mercian.

344
00:29:33,355 --> 00:29:34,982
You do not look like Christians.

345
00:29:35,065 --> 00:29:38,652
We are men from Wealas,
loyal to King Hywel.

346
00:29:38,735 --> 00:29:41,530
Are you an ally or an enemy of Mercia?

347
00:29:42,739 --> 00:29:44,616
We are here to fight Cnut, Lady.

348
00:29:44,700 --> 00:29:49,454
And best The Dane as we have
bested the Saxon for so many years.

349
00:29:49,538 --> 00:29:51,581
And the fyrds?

350
00:29:51,665 --> 00:29:54,918
I put them under the command
of the little bald priest.

351
00:29:55,002 --> 00:29:58,255
I am not bald! I'm certainly not little!

352
00:29:58,338 --> 00:30:02,259
Father Pyrlig! I do not understand.

353
00:30:02,342 --> 00:30:06,305
He rode to Wealas
to beg King Hywel for his army.

354
00:30:06,722 --> 00:30:10,767
Edward sent him to find allies.
I knew he would not abandon me!

355
00:30:10,851 --> 00:30:13,395
No, Lady. It was your mother who sent me.

356
00:30:14,229 --> 00:30:15,897
I have had no word from the King.

357
00:30:19,818 --> 00:30:21,320
Then we fight with what we have.

358
00:30:22,821 --> 00:30:25,073
- It's good to see you, Pyrlig.
- You, too, Lord Uhtred.

359
00:30:25,157 --> 00:30:26,783
Finan! Sihtric!

360
00:30:26,867 --> 00:30:29,244
- Father Pyrlig!
- It's good to see you are alive.

361
00:30:30,454 --> 00:30:33,290
Even with these Welshmen,
we may not be enough.

362
00:30:33,832 --> 00:30:37,669
I know you have summoned Cnut,
but you can still turn away with honor.

363
00:30:39,713 --> 00:30:42,257
No one would condemn you
for leaving an unfair fight.

364
00:30:43,133 --> 00:30:46,011
I do not fight for honor, Uhtred.

365
00:30:46,094 --> 00:30:49,181
I fight because someone must
make a stand against Cnut...

366
00:30:50,307 --> 00:30:51,975
even though I am forbidden.

367
00:30:52,684 --> 00:30:55,520
As a sister, I am defiant,
but as a daughter of Alfred,

368
00:30:55,604 --> 00:30:57,481
I am just doing my duty.

369
00:30:59,107 --> 00:31:03,820
Even if it wasn't made for me,
I can't blindly follow the King's command.

370
00:31:04,821 --> 00:31:06,490
That is something I understand.

371
00:31:07,532 --> 00:31:10,494
Yet I cannot believe
he has left me to face this without him.

372
00:31:12,079 --> 00:31:15,082
I thought, somehow,
he would find it in his heart.

373
00:31:18,460 --> 00:31:20,128
What do I tell my men?

374
00:31:24,674 --> 00:31:29,471
Tell them your brother is close behind us.
They must believe we have a chance.

375
00:31:42,943 --> 00:31:45,529
We've heard from Uhtred
and the Lady Aethelflaed.

376
00:31:45,612 --> 00:31:46,780
Where are they?

377
00:31:47,989 --> 00:31:50,069
They're waiting for you
at a place called Tettenhall.

378
00:31:51,159 --> 00:31:52,244
We go?

379
00:31:54,037 --> 00:31:56,373
It mocks the gods
to give away the advantage!

380
00:32:02,087 --> 00:32:03,630
I will have my revenge.

381
00:32:35,495 --> 00:32:37,205
There are worse places to defend.

382
00:32:38,790 --> 00:32:41,168
With a few more men,
we would stand a chance.

383
00:32:48,592 --> 00:32:49,676
Follow me.

384
00:33:08,028 --> 00:33:09,279
It is prepared.

385
00:33:12,073 --> 00:33:13,116
Will it work?

386
00:33:15,368 --> 00:33:16,411
I do not know.

387
00:33:19,498 --> 00:33:20,707
They're coming.

388
00:33:22,542 --> 00:33:23,835
Get into position!

389
00:33:23,919 --> 00:33:25,128
Follow me!

390
00:33:25,212 --> 00:33:26,713
Mercians to the woods!

391
00:33:26,796 --> 00:33:28,423
To the woods!

392
00:33:37,098 --> 00:33:39,809
If this fails
and there is no escape for you...

393
00:33:41,102 --> 00:33:44,064
promise me you will find a man
you trust to kill you softly.

394
00:33:44,814 --> 00:33:46,608
I have already picked a man.

395
00:33:54,407 --> 00:33:56,660
Be merciful to me, oh God!

396
00:34:02,832 --> 00:34:05,252
When I am afraid,
I will trust in You.

397
00:34:10,632 --> 00:34:13,260
In God whose word I praise.

398
00:34:13,343 --> 00:34:15,470
In God I trust.

399
00:34:15,554 --> 00:34:17,847
I will not be afraid.

400
00:34:20,433 --> 00:34:22,811
What can a man do to me?

401
00:34:23,979 --> 00:34:25,021
Nothing.

402
00:34:26,690 --> 00:34:30,026
For you have delivered my soul from death

403
00:34:30,110 --> 00:34:32,445
and my feet from stumbling...

404
00:34:33,029 --> 00:34:35,782
that I may walk before God.

405
00:34:36,741 --> 00:34:37,951
Something isn't right.

406
00:34:52,841 --> 00:34:56,553
Die! Die!

407
00:34:56,636 --> 00:34:59,764
No! Wait! Hold back!

408
00:35:22,037 --> 00:35:24,080
Now... charge!

409
00:35:27,417 --> 00:35:28,877
With me!

410
00:36:08,875 --> 00:36:10,502
It's a trick!

411
00:36:31,481 --> 00:36:32,816
Where is he?

412
00:36:50,709 --> 00:36:52,585
Give me your hand! Pull!

413
00:37:13,565 --> 00:37:14,691
Uhtred!

414
00:37:14,774 --> 00:37:19,237
Uhtred, I will cut you into pieces,
you murderous coward!

415
00:37:33,710 --> 00:37:34,919
Father!

416
00:37:42,135 --> 00:37:46,347
No shame in having a Dane atop you,
but, honestly, I've seen prettier.

417
00:37:48,767 --> 00:37:50,018
The ridge, Father!

418
00:37:56,566 --> 00:37:58,401
It's Aethelred!

419
00:37:58,485 --> 00:37:59,778
Can they reach us?

420
00:38:08,119 --> 00:38:09,996
Charge!

421
00:38:28,598 --> 00:38:30,225
Who fights alongside Aethelflaed?

422
00:38:30,308 --> 00:38:35,063
The Mercian fyrds, her husband,
even the Welsh.

423
00:38:38,650 --> 00:38:40,193
Christians united.

424
00:38:40,819 --> 00:38:42,987
And without Wessex to lead them forward.

425
00:38:54,332 --> 00:38:56,000
It's the Lady Aethelflaed!

426
00:38:56,084 --> 00:38:57,919
- There she is!
- Surround her!

427
00:38:58,002 --> 00:38:59,587
There are too many of them.

428
00:39:01,172 --> 00:39:02,423
Get her!

429
00:39:06,177 --> 00:39:07,345
Aldhelm.

430
00:39:15,645 --> 00:39:18,231
Withdraw! You will not take her from us!

431
00:39:18,731 --> 00:39:20,400
You do not have the courage.

432
00:39:21,109 --> 00:39:22,443
Aldhelm, you must.

433
00:39:23,069 --> 00:39:24,571
Since you are Alfred's daughter,

434
00:39:24,654 --> 00:39:26,990
I'll let you choose
which of us humps you first.

435
00:39:27,073 --> 00:39:30,326
- Aldhelm, please.
- I can't. I can't.

436
00:39:32,120 --> 00:39:33,663
You Saxons have...

437
00:40:23,963 --> 00:40:25,465
Lord King!

438
00:40:25,548 --> 00:40:27,383
Stay close!

439
00:40:41,648 --> 00:40:43,983
Hold fast, men! Hold your lines!

440
00:40:50,406 --> 00:40:52,867
They are fleeing to the forest!

441
00:40:53,409 --> 00:40:54,702
Stop them!

442
00:40:59,165 --> 00:41:00,249
Uhtred!

443
00:41:19,727 --> 00:41:21,396
What the...

444
00:41:37,704 --> 00:41:39,330
My Lord! My Lord!

445
00:41:45,670 --> 00:41:48,089
Push on, men... to victory!

446
00:42:10,028 --> 00:42:11,070
Uhtred!

447
00:42:13,031 --> 00:42:14,073
Finally.

448
00:42:15,867 --> 00:42:16,909
Fight me.

449
00:42:17,744 --> 00:42:18,953
Fight me!

450
00:42:35,428 --> 00:42:36,888
Murderer!

451
00:42:53,613 --> 00:42:55,031
You killed my firstborn.

452
00:42:56,074 --> 00:43:00,328
You killed my boy! Why?

453
00:43:01,079 --> 00:43:03,331
It was fair revenge for Ragnar!

454
00:43:03,414 --> 00:43:04,999
Ragnar!

455
00:43:09,670 --> 00:43:13,341
Ragnar was weak...
and I needed him to die!

456
00:43:13,424 --> 00:43:15,968
But my son... my son was innocent!

457
00:43:21,974 --> 00:43:23,142
Brida...

458
00:43:25,853 --> 00:43:27,230
Give me your seax!

459
00:43:30,191 --> 00:43:31,275
Give me your seax!

460
00:43:53,422 --> 00:43:55,466
You sent Aethelwold to kill Ragnar?

461
00:43:58,427 --> 00:43:59,512
Because...

462
00:44:00,429 --> 00:44:03,516
Because we're destined to be together.
You know this.

463
00:44:05,601 --> 00:44:07,186
Please, my love.

464
00:44:22,326 --> 00:44:23,619
Your boys live.

465
00:44:25,705 --> 00:44:29,667
The body your man saw was a Mercian,
killed by Danish hands.

466
00:44:30,418 --> 00:44:33,838
- Both... both survive?
- Both.

467
00:44:35,423 --> 00:44:37,592
But you will not live
to see them grow old.

468
00:44:43,514 --> 00:44:45,141
You should not have trusted him.

469
00:45:14,629 --> 00:45:16,380
Keep up!

470
00:45:35,316 --> 00:45:36,984
Send me to Valhalla.

471
00:45:41,322 --> 00:45:42,949
They will take you as a prisoner.

472
00:45:43,032 --> 00:45:47,745
That's worse than death.
Please, I cannot be a slave.

473
00:45:49,163 --> 00:45:51,290
Let me die with honor
here on the battlefield.

474
00:45:52,458 --> 00:45:54,502
You owe me that, Uhtred.

475
00:45:56,671 --> 00:45:59,298
I want to be with Ragnar. Please, Uhtred.

476
00:46:01,133 --> 00:46:02,385
Please.

477
00:46:05,012 --> 00:46:06,472
Take the pagan bitch!

478
00:46:12,019 --> 00:46:13,229
Brida.

479
00:46:40,715 --> 00:46:45,136
King Hywel,
you have done all Christians proud.

480
00:46:45,219 --> 00:46:46,762
It is an honor to meet you.

481
00:46:46,846 --> 00:46:49,765
And I am pleased
you were able to make the battle, Lord.

482
00:46:51,142 --> 00:46:53,644
Well, we would not have won
without you and your men.

483
00:46:54,186 --> 00:46:55,646
I am most grateful.

484
00:46:55,730 --> 00:46:58,274
And your generous rewards are appreciated.

485
00:46:59,817 --> 00:47:04,155
Your priest conveyed to me
your kind offer of the spoils of battle.

486
00:47:07,325 --> 00:47:11,078
Of course.
It is the least your bravery deserves.

487
00:47:11,162 --> 00:47:13,497
May it strengthen our new union.

488
00:47:14,415 --> 00:47:16,417
As we are united in faith...

489
00:47:17,168 --> 00:47:21,464
let us be united in prosperity
and security!

490
00:47:23,049 --> 00:47:25,968
I promise you, we shall feast tonight!

491
00:47:29,055 --> 00:47:33,476
There will be no alliance
and no more favors.

492
00:47:34,560 --> 00:47:37,688
The people of Wealas
do not need Saxon help.

493
00:48:14,558 --> 00:48:16,060
The Lord favored us.

494
00:48:17,853 --> 00:48:20,231
I've just sent Brida to her doom.

495
00:48:20,314 --> 00:48:22,066
It is battle.

496
00:48:22,149 --> 00:48:25,319
What matters is we both survived
and Mercia is safe.

497
00:48:29,407 --> 00:48:31,117
- My Lord King.
- My Lord.

498
00:48:31,742 --> 00:48:33,035
Sire.

499
00:48:33,119 --> 00:48:34,161
My Lord...

500
00:48:34,245 --> 00:48:37,164
- He dares to walk amongst the fallen?
- Do not.

501
00:48:37,790 --> 00:48:39,333
There has been enough fighting.

502
00:48:40,584 --> 00:48:41,836
Your men need you.

503
00:48:59,520 --> 00:49:03,858
Lady, the triumph is all yours.

504
00:49:04,525 --> 00:49:07,611
You led us to a great victory
they will speak of for years to come.

505
00:49:07,695 --> 00:49:10,197
And I thank you I am alive to see it.

506
00:49:11,657 --> 00:49:13,617
I probably wasn't the man for that task.

507
00:49:19,457 --> 00:49:21,750
Edward, thank you.

508
00:49:22,835 --> 00:49:25,171
If it were not for you,
I would be amongst the dead.

509
00:49:25,254 --> 00:49:27,590
I came despite my better judgment.

510
00:49:28,841 --> 00:49:31,427
I do not take your defiance lightly.

511
00:49:32,344 --> 00:49:36,098
- Yes, but surely it was a great victory.
- With a great loss of many men.

512
00:49:38,142 --> 00:49:39,518
Steapa is dead.

513
00:49:41,520 --> 00:49:42,813
- No.
- Yes.

514
00:49:43,355 --> 00:49:46,567
The man who has stood since our childhood
like a giant oak.

515
00:49:46,650 --> 00:49:48,861
He stood with our father, then with us.

516
00:49:48,944 --> 00:49:51,822
Now he's been taken
in a battle of your making,

517
00:49:51,906 --> 00:49:54,325
sacrificed for your husband's ambition
and for yours.

518
00:49:54,408 --> 00:49:56,243
No, I have no ambition.

519
00:49:56,327 --> 00:49:58,245
You seek to be loved by all...

520
00:49:59,455 --> 00:50:03,125
chronicled for your bravery,
no matter if it costs the blood of men.

521
00:50:04,585 --> 00:50:07,213
- That is not true.
- Yes, it is.

522
00:50:07,296 --> 00:50:10,716
You've chosen Mercia
over the kingdom of Alfred.

523
00:50:12,092 --> 00:50:15,012
I suggest you do not return south
for a long time.

524
00:50:16,222 --> 00:50:18,432
You should not exile me from Winchester.

525
00:50:18,516 --> 00:50:21,685
I fear you would
not be welcome there, Lady.

526
00:50:23,562 --> 00:50:26,440
The widows of these men
will not forgive you easily.

527
00:50:27,316 --> 00:50:33,197
Still, you may receive adoration
in this place.

528
00:50:34,323 --> 00:50:37,826
It may be some compensation.

529
00:50:38,786 --> 00:50:42,456
None of this was done
for anything but love of my country!

530
00:50:47,169 --> 00:50:49,171
Come away from this place, Lord King.

531
00:50:57,471 --> 00:50:59,181
I have been made to look a fool...

532
00:51:00,307 --> 00:51:03,852
unable to reward my own men,
paying tribute to the Welsh.

533
00:51:05,563 --> 00:51:06,939
This will be made right.

534
00:51:08,315 --> 00:51:10,943
What excuses did he make
for his cowardice?

535
00:51:12,611 --> 00:51:14,989
He wanted to avoid bloodshed for his men.

536
00:51:15,489 --> 00:51:17,199
Which created more bloodshed.

537
00:51:18,409 --> 00:51:20,077
- I have to speak with him.
- No!

538
00:51:20,661 --> 00:51:21,996
At least not now.

539
00:51:23,706 --> 00:51:26,667
The Danes are defeated.
Let us just enjoy the peace...

540
00:51:27,835 --> 00:51:29,169
just for one night.

541
00:51:33,799 --> 00:51:35,426
I will do as you ask...

542
00:51:37,636 --> 00:51:39,179
just for one night.

543
00:51:59,908 --> 00:52:02,369
Let us go, take advantage of the chaos.

544
00:52:02,453 --> 00:52:05,873
- He can believe you died in battle.
- No. I have half killed myself fighting.

545
00:52:05,956 --> 00:52:09,084
I will find him and I will beg him.

546
00:52:09,168 --> 00:52:13,088
He will never forgive us for what
we have done. It is over for us, brother.

547
00:52:13,172 --> 00:52:16,175
Clear a path! Move! Stand aside!

548
00:52:22,014 --> 00:52:24,850
Lord Aethelred is wounded. Fetch a healer!

549
00:52:24,874 --> 00:52:26,874
http://hiqve.com/

